cc:Work.dc:title: Inserse Power Function
cc:Work.dc:description: Graphical interpretation of reverse power operations. The (twodimensional) inverse image of z is hatched and outlined in the figure, in the shown example it is z = [2, 3]. A, for given intervals y and z find every x with x^y ∩ z ≠ Ø. B, for given intervals x and z find every y with x^y ∩ z ≠ Ø.
